
                                            Cyril Ramaphosa secured 423 branch nominations and his rival Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma managed 61.
                                         CAPE TOWN - The African National Congress (ANC) in the Eastern Cape has nominated Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa to be the next party president. Ramaphosa secured 423 branch nominations and his rival Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma managed 61.  The provincial general council was held at the East London City Hall. The race for the deputy presidency was a close call, with ANC Treasurer General Zweli Mkhize receiving 193 nominations and Mpumalanga Chairperson David Mabuza winning 190.